Package: hhsurveydata
Title: Data processing tools for DHS and other household surveys
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(person("Jeff", "Eaton", email = "jeffrey.eaton@imperial.ac.uk", role = c("aut", "cre")),
             person("Bruno", "Masquelier", email = "bruno.masquelier@uclouvain.be", role = "aut"))
Description: This package includes tools for processing and analysing data from household
    surveys. Initially developed for for processing and analysis of demographic and HIV
    indicators from Demographic and Health Surveys (DHS) and Multiple Indicator Cluster
    Surveys (MICS).
Depends: R (>= 3.2.0),
Imports:
    survival (>= 2.39),
    survey (>= 2.33),
    reshape2 (>= 1.4.3),
    stats
Suggests: 
    foreign,
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    testthat,
    covr
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
VignetteBuilder: knitr
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
